text.tspan: Lord, I love You! Draw me with Your beauty
Consecration — Constrained by the Lord’s Love
Lord, I open to Your working today;
Saturate each part, Lord without reservation.
Lord, I offer You my full coop’ration;
Lord, that You alone possess my whole heart today.
Lord, I do thank You for dying for me;
Lord, Your precious blood has redeemed me from all dross;
Lord, you bore my sins on that old rugged cross.
Lord, You sacrificed Your whole life fully for me.
Lord, I’ve been constrained by God’s love through You.
Master, how can I ever turn away from You?
Lord, I do love You; I give myself to You.
Lord, I consecrate my whole life fully to You.
